items.description: Wheeler, Rawson and Co. are overjoyed to offer this most celebrated and comprehensive ensemble. Constructed by our nation’s finest tailors for the world’s greatest bounty hunters, no outfit is more comfortable, more fashionable, more suitable for the pursuit of degenerates and villains. When the law requires that you keep your pistols holstered, now is the opportunity to kill with looks.

items.description: The Gypsy Cob is a hardy, strong and intelligent breed distinctive for its thick mane, tail and heavy feathering on the legs. Standing 14-15 hands high, they are highly sought after for their temperament and intuition. Originally bred by the Romany Gypsy to pull caravans throughout England and Ireland, they are a luxurious breed, fearless and powerful with great stamina.

items.description: Imagine a leisurely ride across the pastoral prairie, accentuated by ear-splitting explosions and screams of merriment that typically accompany discharge of firearms. While some extoll false refinements that hunting should only be done on horseback in riding regalia, hounds baying in the distance, this is an unqualified condemnation by conceited Englishmen. Our Hunting Wagon ensures a smooth ride, with steel rockers and Norway iron body loops. The good, honest wheels with 1 inch tread are sturdy and true. A solid wood construction for transporting animal pelts and carcasses.

items.description: When exercising your authority over matters or altercations in your hamlet or homestead, the Prison Wagon is the perfect vehicle for delivering rabble-rousers to justice. Whether it be punishing a son or daughter upbraiding their elders, relocating indigenous peoples who lust to burn your dwellings to the ground, or ameliorating tempers of workers unhappy about pay, the Prison Wagon is just the vehicle to provide safety and security for both passengers and driver. It is manufactured by one of the oldest most reliable manufacturers available.

items.description: We present to you the preeminent ensemble in our workwear line: The Wilkesboro. Upon first showing of this outfit to the public at an exhibition near our warehouse, several individuals were forcibly restrained, so unbridled was their excitement. True, it causes temporary dement upon first donning this ensemble, and it will provide hours of private gratification. The Wilkesboro establishes one as a member of the top tier in the spirits profession.

items.description: We humbly present to you this compendious introduction to the highest, most prized outfit in our Collector collection. It features habiliments that are the finest available on any continent. Our aim with this collection is to celebrate those that are glorious exceptions with sturdy virtues, noble and hardworking, not predisposed to excess of drink and causing a rumpus. Surely it takes one such as you, possessed by honesty, cunning and genius, to purchase this top class Collector outfit from the finest purveyors of attire, Wheeler, Rawson and Co.

items.description: We present to you The Carthage. No better ensemble for the fugitive recovery trade exists. Our quality tradesmen clothing cannot be matched. Top quality garments and accessories suitable for the pursuit of unsavory characters can, at times, seem slightly expensive. However, those that register complaint about such matters have likely gone wholly unrewarded in life, never having experienced the comfort and character of luxury goods. An outfit ought to speak of your profile in the community, highlighting your class and profession.

With the Kennewick, the wearer instantly exhibits alacrity for which this honorable profession is distinguished. The free life, dressed in a perfect ensemble from Wheeler, Rawson and Co., truly stirs the soul.

It makes the timid strong, the will resolute. While the crack of a pistol speaks volumes, so too does a perfectly fitting ensemble from Wheeler, Rawson and Co.

items.description: Frugality is a doubtful virtue, and many who count pennies could instead be counting much larger denominations had they the foresight to order this splendid ensemble for the Trader profession. Its purchase might insight discovery of the passions in life, where nebulous ideas burn bright. It is clothing for the steadfast and hardworking, one who refuses leisurely plantation life, where idlers lazily drink draughts of wine at an astonishing hour, doting about like a swan in a tea garden or polo pleasure ground.

items.description: We call your attention to this handsome, captivating outfit for our customers engaged in the Collector trade. Too often Collectors are weighed down, their bodies girt with excessive adornments not truly needed for the pursuit at hand. Should anyone question our volubility regarding this ensemble, we seek to rest your mind at ease. It is one of the finest Collector outfits on offer. The purchaser can confidently claim patronage of the Collector class once donning these spectacular garments.

Place your order today.

items.description: We take great pleasure in presenting this outfit to you. In the process of designing an ensemble meant for the fugitive recovery trade, we received quite a bit of correspondence regarding the working conditions and compensation of the profession. Many are wounded, maimed or killed for reasonably low bounties and can scarcely afford a bottle of whiskey and a coquettish companion for the evening after a successful bounty has been turned in. With this in mind we are offering it at the lowest price possible.

items.description: We present to you this one of a kind Collector outfit specially designed for the trade. Humankind is a long-suffering species, plagued by maladies, pestilence, threats from scurrilous outsiders and assaults to vanity. True wisdom and happiness are arrived at through instruments of accomplishment: whether fine ensembles or gilded combs, or curios, gimcrack and gewgaws. You will never find a despondent man or woman in a new outfit from Wheeler, Rawson and Co.

items.description: Unquestionably, our tradesman attire is the best on offer for this vocation. Undoubtedly, for those in the profession of trading animal skins and pelts, appearance is everything, for we are visual creatures who determine the trustworthiness of an individual in mere seconds. Appearance is second only to aroma, for nobody prefers trade with someone whose bouquet resembles a ruminant animal. Order this ensemble today, with haste, and it will become abundantly clear that, indeed, Wheeler, Rawson and Co. are the arbiters of excellence.

Admirers of the Sagemoor will profess themselves truly charmed upon first gazing at their reflection in a looking glass or tranquil pond. It is designed to perfectly demonstrate the internal quality of the soul as one seeks to better understand the country, cosmos, and natural history.

items.description: At Wheeler, Rawson and Co. we believe that the study of fauna and flora is a decisive step in the path of genteel civilization. Strikingly original, the garments and accessories that make up the Tilliston instantly demonstrate fidelity as a pupil of Naturalist studies, a developed love of nature and a robust knowledge of the order of things. The cut of these garments perfectly suits the tracking and tranquilizing of beasts, their dissection and study, as well as the collection of herbs and flowers for medicines and tinctures.

items.description: One of the world’s oldest horse breeds, the Kladruber is a rare breed from Eastern Europe. A Czech breed, they are often used as a fancy carriage horse, and are suitable for pulling a wide array of carts and wagons. They stand between 16-17 hands high. Their nature is calm, and they are known for maintaining a good speed in a harness. The shoulders are upright, the back long, and the croup short. They are a very recognizable breed and will surely provide great service for years to come.

items.description: This hardy breed hails from South America, where in 1540 a shipment of pure-bred Spanish Andalusian stallions were set free as the Spaniards abandoned Buenos Aires. The feral horse population that resulted was able to live in extreme heat and cold with little water or grass. They are an intelligent breed, averaging 14-15 hands high, and have high stamina, making them perfect for the traveller who is required to go long distances over rough terrain. They have sound, hard feet, a strong body, sloping shoulders and a muscular neck.

items.description: The Breton is a powerful breed and an instant favorite amongst horse enthusiasts. The name derives from the Breton region of France where they were bred for thousands of years. Standing around 16 hands high, Breton horses were ridden by the Celts, who were tribes of Gauls, Gaels, Galations that drank out of goblets and sent messages attached to birds. They are a bulky, heavyset breed capable of draft work, but they are also used as war horses due to their gait and disposition.

items.description: The Norfolk Roadster first arrived in the United States around 1822 and has since become one of the most popular horse breeds today due, in part, to its versatility and ability to travel great distances at significant speed. Whether for riding, racing or use as a carriage horse, the Norfolk Roadster is a quite influential trotting breed and is known to have an excellent temperament.
